revision.text: ==English== {{wikipedia|mul=Xochistlahuaca (municipality)}} ===Etymology=== Borrowed from {{bor|en|es|Xochistlahuaca}}, from a {{der|en|azc-nah}} language; equivalent to {{cog|nci|xōchitl|t=flower}} + {{m|nci|ixtlāhuacān|t=plain}}. The Nahuan word is a {{glossary|calque}} from Amuzgo; compare {{cog|azg|Suntjaaꞌ|t=flower plain}}. ===Proper noun=== {{en-proper noun}} # {{place|en|town|s/Guerrero|c/Mexico}}. # {{place|en|municipality|s/Guerrero|c/Mexico|capital=Xochistlahuaca}}.
